t: To the chief Musician, Alâ€“taschith, A Psalm or Song of Asaph.
Unto*p thee, O God, do we give thanks, unto thee do we give thanks: for that thy name is near thy wondrous works declare.
When*p I shall receive the congregation I will judge uprightly.
The*p earth and all the inhabitants thereof are dissolved: I bear up the pillars of it. Selah.
I*p said unto the fools, Deal not foolishly: and to the wicked, Lift not up the horn:
Lift*p not up your horn on high: speak not with a stiff neck.
For*p promotion cometh neither from the east, nor from the west, nor from the south.
But*p God is the judge: he putteth down one, and setteth up another.

For*p in the hand of the Lord*s there is a cup, and the wine is red; it is full of mixture; and he poureth out of the same: but the dregs thereof, all the wicked of the earth shall wring them out, and drink them.
But*p I will declare for ever; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.
All*p the horns of the wicked also will I cut off; but the horns of the righteous shall be exalted.
